{
  "doc_id": "51678",
  "text": "Cupressus sempervirens L., a medium-sized evergreen tree, is an ornamental tree belonging to the Cupressaceae family. It is native to the eastern Mediterranean region [CITATION_1] ). Traditionally C. sempervirens L. is used for the cure of colds, flu, evils throat, rheumatism and also used as antiseptics and antispasmodics [CITATION_2] . It comprises of tannin and used as antipyretic, constipating, diaphoretic and astringent. The methanolic and other extracts were showed good antibacterial activity [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The essential oil of the leaves showed a remarkable antimicrobial activity [CITATION_6] ).",
